description:
&lt;p&gt;Beds &amp; Herts Breast Screening Services are looking for&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Advanced practitioner – A4C BAND 7 - 37.5hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for an advanced practitioner with a post graduate qualification in breast interventional procedures to join our friendly team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We would also consider applications from radiographers with a post graduate certificate in mammography who have an interest in training for the interventional qualification.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Beds &amp; Herts Breast Screening Service is one of the largest units in the country and provides breast screening and assessment services to women living across Bedfordshire and Hertfordshire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be expected to support symptomatic, screening, assessment and follow up clinics in the Breast Unit at the Luton and Dunstable Hospital and screening on 4 mobile units. The ability to get to the mobiles is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Opportunities for role progression form an exciting part of our continuing service development plan. We currently have 10 mammographers working in advanced practice and have recently trained a consultant radiographer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We can offer you the chance to join a great friendly team, aiming to provide the best service to our women.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post has a GOQ under the Sex Discrimination Act 1975 Section 7 (2) and is therefore restricted to female applicants only.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 1.35em;&quot;&gt;For further details / informal visits contact: please contact Anne- Marie Leach, deputy Screening Manager on 01582 497593 - anne-marie.leach@ldh.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
